      "rationale": "The three QoIs selected correspond to the clinically relevant failure modes for pedicle screw constructs under compression-bending: initial stiffness governs load sharing, yield force marks onset of permanent deformation, and force at 40 mm represents post-yield structural capacity. All are directly computable from both FEA and experiment."
